title: U.S., Britain launch new wave of military strikes in Yemen
description: The operation follows a large-scale attack on Iranian forces and their affiliates in Iraq and Syria, retribution for the killing of three U.S. troops in Jordan.

title: House to vote on standalone Israel aid bill, setting up showdown with Senate
description: House Republicans are proposing a $17.6 billion bill for Israel that doesn’t include any aid for Ukraine, as Senate plans wider funding for border security and aiding foreign democracies.

title: Senegal’s president delays elections indefinitely
description: President Macky Sall’s decision to delay the vote, just hours before official campaigning was scheduled to start, could fuel a new round of protests in Senegal.

title: U.S. strikes in Syria and Iraq kill dozens of militants
description: The strikes were the start of what U.S. officials said will be a multiday campaign as the Biden administration attempts to respond to the killing of three U.S. soldiers without escalating regional conflict.

title: El Salvador is set to reelect ‘world’s coolest dictator.’ Here’s what to know.
description: Polls point to a landslide victory for Nayib Bukele, the 42-year-old incumbent known for his offensive against El Salvador’s gangs.

title: N. Ireland gets its first Sinn Féin first minister in historic shift
description: After two years without a government, Northern Ireland’s lawmakers return and will name Michelle O’Neill as first minister in power-sharing structure.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: U.S. attacks will go on at ‘times and places of our choosing,’ Biden says
description: U.S. forces hit 85 targets in Iraq and Syria that included command and control centers, as well as weapons storage sites, operated by Iran-backed militia groups.

title: Israel says it will expand operations in Rafah, Gaza’s last refuge
description: Humanitarian organizations say further conflict in the area runs the risk of causing significant harm to the more than 1.4 million Palestinians sheltering there.
